SIMPLE: self-adjusting
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Self-adjusting
<hw>Self`-ad*just"ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<fld>(Mach.)</fld> <def>Capable of assuming a desired position or
condition with relation to other parts, under varying circumstances,
without requiring to be adjusted by hand; -- said of a piece in
machinery.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Self-adjusting bearing</b></col> <fld>(Shafting)</fld>,
<cd>a bearing which is supported in such a manner that it may tip to
accomodate flexure or displacement of the shaft.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Self-admiration</ent>⟦br⟧
